originalText.text:
Came to this cool ramen place in Times Square with the family.  I love the setup of the restaurant and how you have your own little booth.

Our waiter was super friendly and truly enjoyed the ramen.  I had the veggie one which was good.  You also must try the matcha dessert because it was definitely enjoyable!

Also great that you can make reservations on the Yelp app which makes my life so much easier!

originalText.text: If I could give them 20 stars I would.  The food was phenomenal.   Service was quick and attentive.   They take the time to explain the menu and dishes.  The price was great for the amount of food you get.  I ordered the curry ramen and OMG it was soooo good!  My daughter ordered the black garlic tonkatsu ramen and that broth is the best I ever tasted.  Hands down these are the ramen experts!  I highly recommend them!!

originalText.text: We walked in this evening, without a reservation, and were seated immediately. We were brought water quickly, then beverages. I tried the peach jelly canned drink. It was bizarre but intriguing, I was happy to try something new. Food wise- gyoza were fresh and flavorful. My husband had a bowl of ramen which was rich and tasty. I ordered the eel, avocado, and cucumber rice burger. The "burger" was huge, I ended up taking off one of the rice patties but it was on point with flavor. I did appreciate the plastic gloves to pick the burger up, it was a nice touch. Service was quick and friendly.

originalText.text:
Food is great.  Had ramen combo deal.  Excellent appetizer and dessert.   Good value.  Good atmosphere.

Service is somewhat hit or miss.  Our waiter somewhat rudely slammed a bottle of chilled sake in front of me, despite the menu says it is served hot and I specifically requested so 30 sec earlier.  Appetizers came up later than ramen.

So, almost perfect but not quite there yet.  It's about the small intangible details, too.

originalText.text: We visited the Times Sq. location for the first time as my daughter was wanting to have the omurice which is a difficult dish to find (done well) in NYC. When we walked in we were transported by the authentic ambiance on the restaurant. There is stool bar seating in the front and private dining seating in the back. We made reservations so were accommodated in the private seating area. I throughly enjoyed the private dining experience. You are provided with a call button to alert the waiter when you are ready to order, need assistance, and are ready for your bill. It is a courteous touch that adds to the private dining experience. We ordered the Kyushu Tonkotsu Shio Ramen with Black Garlic, Spicy Kyushu Tonkotsu Ramen, Omurice with demiglaze, Omurice with Pork Tonkatsu and curry sauce. To drink we had the Thai Iced Tea, and a Kyoto White Yuzu. For dessert we ordered the ube cake. Everything was served promptly. Both ramen dishes were of a generous portion with chewy wavy noodles and creamy broth just like I like my ramen. The black garlic really added depth to the dish. Highly recommend it. The omurice dishes were good. Both sauces were delicious but the preferred sauce was the demiglaze. The Thai iced tea was creamy and refreshing. The Kyoto White Yuzu beer was very light with a hint of sweetness. It was a nice pallet cleanser from the rich broth and curry.  The star of the night was hands down the ube cake.  There were more than ten layers of thin pastry with a slight sweet and rich ube cream layered in between. It was a very light and decadent sweet ending to a overall good meal. We were not rushed and sat until we were ready to call for our bill. It was a very pleasant and authentic experience. I would highly recommend it.
